WEBVTT

00:01.968 --> 00:04.038
THE HUDSON INN
HAD A CANCELATION,

00:04.038 --> 00:06.540
AND WE CAN RENEW
OUR WEDDING VOWS APRIL 20th.

00:06.540 --> 00:08.709
NO, ANGIE.
YOU KNOW IT'S TAX TIME.

00:08.709 --> 00:10.644
I DON'T THINK THE IRS
WOULD APPRECIATE

00:10.644 --> 00:13.114
SOMEBODY ON A PAYMENT PLAN
THROWING A HUGE WEDDING.

00:13.114 --> 00:14.582
WE'RE ON
A PAYMENT PLAN?

00:14.582 --> 00:18.586
YOU SAID, "DO THE TAXES."
I DID THE TAXES.

00:18.586 --> 00:19.953
HOW MUCH DO WE OWE?

00:19.953 --> 00:21.389
NOT MUCH.

00:21.389 --> 00:23.791
BUT FOR A VERY LONG TIME.

00:25.459 --> 00:27.361
OKAY, THEN,
HOW ABOUT MAY?

00:27.361 --> 00:29.963
THE BOTANICAL GARDENS
HAS AN OPENING.

00:29.963 --> 00:32.232
I THINK
IT WOULD BE SO BEAUTIFUL

00:32.232 --> 00:35.069
IF WE GOT REMARRIED
SURROUNDED BY FLOWERS.

00:35.069 --> 00:37.238
YOU KNOW MY MOM'S
ALLERGIC TO BEES.

00:37.238 --> 00:38.706
SO? WE RENEW OUR LOVE.

00:38.706 --> 00:41.175
YOUR MOM GETS STUNG
AND HER THROAT CLOSES UP.

00:41.175 --> 00:43.811
[ Voice breaking ]
IT'S A PERFECT DAY FOR ME.

00:46.614 --> 00:49.983
WHY IS YOUR BOSS OUTSIDE
WITH A BOTTLE OF CHAMPAGNE?

00:49.983 --> 00:51.785
HEY.

00:51.785 --> 00:53.254
JACK!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

00:53.254 --> 00:54.622
I GOT GREAT NEWS.

00:54.622 --> 00:57.024
THE JUDGE BOUGHT
YOUR COLD-MEDICINE STORY,

00:57.024 --> 00:58.959
AND YOU GOT OUT
OF YOUR D.U.I.?

00:58.959 --> 01:00.661
I WISH.
I HAD TO WALK OVER HERE.

01:03.964 --> 01:05.465
I'M IN LOVE.

01:05.465 --> 01:08.102
I MET THE WOMAN OF MY DREAMS,
AND I'M GETTING MARRIED.

01:08.102 --> 01:09.870
[ GASPS ]
JACK, THAT'S GREAT!

01:09.870 --> 01:11.372
YEAH, CONGRATULATIONS.

01:11.372 --> 01:13.507
ANGIE, I WANT YOU
TO PLAN THE WEDDING.

01:13.507 --> 01:16.977
ME? REALLY?
I'M HONORED.

01:16.977 --> 01:19.813
THAT'S TERRIFIC.
YOU GOT TWO WEEKS.

01:19.813 --> 01:22.450
IS THAT HOW LONG IT TAKES
THE BOAT TO GET HERE

01:22.450 --> 01:24.084
FROM THE PHILIPPINES?

01:24.084 --> 01:26.854
JACK, I DON'T KNOW
IF THAT'S ENOUGH TIME

01:26.854 --> 01:28.489
TO PUT TOGETHER
A WEDDING.

01:28.489 --> 01:31.659
MY FIANCÃ©E'S MOM IS SICK.
SHE DOESN'T HAVE A LOT OF TIME.

01:31.659 --> 01:34.162
WE WANT HER TO BE THERE,
SO, PLEASE.

01:34.162 --> 01:35.763
OKAY, JACK.

01:35.763 --> 01:38.266
FOR YOU, I WILL THROW
A WONDERFUL WEDDING.

01:38.266 --> 01:40.268
BUT I'M GETTING
PRETTY BUSY

01:40.268 --> 01:43.204
NOW THAT I'M LISTED FIRST
IN THE PHONE BOOK.

01:43.204 --> 01:47.141
THANK YOU FOR CHOOSING
AAAAANGIE'S WEDDINGS.

01:48.809 --> 01:52.513
AM I TIRED OF HEARING THAT?
I AAAAAM!

01:52.513 --> 01:55.583
COME ON, JACK,
LET'S CELEBRATE OUTSIDE.

01:55.583 --> 01:58.852
IF YOU WANT ME,
I'LL BE OOOOOUT HERE.

02:01.955 --> 02:03.291
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

02:03.291 --> 02:05.459
SHE HAS NO IDEA
WE JUST SET HER UP

02:05.459 --> 02:07.995
TO PLAN HER OWN
WEDDING-VOW RENEWAL.

02:07.995 --> 02:09.463
WHAT'S THE NEXT STEP?

02:09.463 --> 02:11.699
I'LL FIND OUT
EVERYTHING ANGIE LIKES,

02:11.699 --> 02:14.468
THEN YOU ASK FOR IT
LIKE IT'S FOR YOUR OWN WEDDING.

02:14.468 --> 02:17.905
THAT WAY, I'LL SURPRISE HER
WITH THE CEREMONY OF HER DREAMS.

02:17.905 --> 02:21.008
GEORGE, I'VE LIED
TO MY SHARE OF WOMEN --

02:21.008 --> 02:22.743
NEVER TO DO
SOMETHING NICE.

02:22.743 --> 02:25.446
"YEAH, I AM
A BILLIONAIRE."

02:25.446 --> 02:28.849
"IF THAT CAMERA WAS RUNNING,
THE RED LIGHT WOULD BE ON."

02:30.618 --> 02:35.623
"AFTERWARDS, I'LL TAKE YOU
TO DINNER ANYPLACE YOU WANT."

02:35.623 --> 02:37.725
I JUST WANT TO THANK YOU
FOR HELPING ME.

02:37.725 --> 02:40.394
AFTER THE WEDDING,
LET ME TAKE YOU TO DINNER

02:40.394 --> 02:41.695
ANYPLACE YOU WANT.

02:43.831 --> 02:45.233
NICE.

02:45.233 --> 02:47.167
I COULD SO
GET YOU INTO BED.

02:49.270 --> 02:51.805
[ INTRO TO WAR'S "LOW RIDER"
PLAYS ]

02:55.609 --> 03:01.181
* ALL MY FRIENDS
KNOW THE LOW RIDER *

03:12.926 --> 03:14.428
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

03:14.428 --> 03:17.431
HERE'S A LIST OF STUFF
ANGIE WANTS FOR THE CEREMONY.

03:17.431 --> 03:18.899
WHEN YOU
COME OVER TONIGHT,

03:18.899 --> 03:20.934
JUST PRETEND THIS
IS THE STUFF YOU WANT.

03:20.934 --> 03:23.737
CALLA LILIES, CANDLES --
THAT SOUNDS ROMANTIC.

03:23.737 --> 03:26.006
WAIT TILL THE CEREMONY,
WHEN WE KISS,

03:26.006 --> 03:29.109
WE FINALLY SAY "I DO,"
AND THE BAND PLAYS OUR SONG.

03:29.109 --> 03:33.514
UH, YOU SURE YOU TWO WANT
TO RUSH INTO THIS MARRIAGE?

03:33.514 --> 03:35.549
YOU WANT TO
EXPLAIN THIS?

03:35.549 --> 03:38.051
OKAY, MOM,
IF I TELL YOU SOMETHING,

03:38.051 --> 03:40.988
DO YOU PROMISE TO KEEP
YOUR MOUTH SHUT ABOUT IT?

03:40.988 --> 03:42.456
WELL, LET'S SEE, GEORGE.

03:42.456 --> 03:46.126
FOR 30 YEARS, I HAD YOU
THINKING YOUR DAD WAS DEAD.

03:46.126 --> 03:47.495
SO I GUESS I CAN HANDLE

03:47.495 --> 03:51.332
WHATEVER THIS TEA-PARTY SECRET
OF YOURS IS.

03:51.332 --> 03:54.302
ANGIE THINKS
SHE'S PLANNING JACK'S WEDDING,

03:54.302 --> 03:56.404
BUT IT'S REALLY
OUR VOW RENEWAL.

03:56.404 --> 03:59.973
I CANNOT BELIEVE
YOU ARE REMARRYING YOUR WIFE!

03:59.973 --> 04:03.544
WHY DON'T YOU JUST GIVE ANGIE
ALL OF YOUR MONEY

04:03.544 --> 04:06.480
AND CUT OFF YOUR MANHOOD
IN SHAME?

04:06.480 --> 04:08.849
BECAUSE I'M NOT
ONE OF YOUR DATES, MOM.

04:13.120 --> 04:14.922
GEORGE, WHAT'S ANGIE
DOING HERE?

04:14.922 --> 04:17.757
SHE WANTS TO GO OVER
SOME WEDDING DETAILS.

04:17.757 --> 04:20.461
NOT HERE -- I DON'T WANT
THE PEOPLE IN THE OFFICE

04:20.461 --> 04:22.029
TO KNOW I'M GETTING MARRIED.

04:22.029 --> 04:23.397
BUT THAT'S OUR COVER.

04:23.397 --> 04:25.633
FOR YOUR WIFE --
NOT THE PEOPLE AT WORK.

04:25.633 --> 04:28.502
LOOK, GEORGE, THERE'S
A SPECIAL LADY ON THE FLOOR

04:28.502 --> 04:30.237
WHO WILL BE VERY SURPRISED

04:30.237 --> 04:33.240
TO LEARN THAT
JACKHAMMER'S OFF THE MARKET.

04:33.240 --> 04:36.877
[ LAUGHS ]
JACKHAMMER...

04:36.877 --> 04:38.479
YOU'RE SERIOUS.

04:38.479 --> 04:40.448
LUCKY LADY.

04:40.448 --> 04:43.617
LET'S GET ANGIE.
WE'LL KEEP THIS ON THE DOWN LOW.

04:43.617 --> 04:45.653
Ernie:
GUESS WHAT, EVERYBODY?!

04:45.653 --> 04:47.621
JACK'S GETTING MARRIED!

04:50.391 --> 04:53.293
ANGIE JUST TOLD ME
THE GREAT NEWS.

04:57.064 --> 04:58.499
I'M SORRY, MA'AM.

04:58.499 --> 05:01.969
I JUST COULDN'T GIVE YOU
THAT RAISE.

05:01.969 --> 05:04.938
WHY DON'T WE TALK
IN THE OFFICE, ANGIE.

05:08.609 --> 05:12.813
OH, COME ON, SHORTY.
I'M STILL YOUR BOO.

05:14.682 --> 05:17.451
I WAS ON MY WAY TO THE FLORIST,
AND I REALIZED --

05:17.451 --> 05:20.554
I DON'T KNOW WHAT FLOWERS
JACK'S FIANCÃ©E LIKES.

05:20.554 --> 05:22.456
I DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT HER.

05:22.456 --> 05:23.891
WHAT'S HER NAME?

05:23.891 --> 05:26.360
OH, IT'S --
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL NAME.

05:26.360 --> 05:27.761
IT'S, UH...

05:27.761 --> 05:30.263
DELL.

05:30.263 --> 05:31.699
DELL?

05:31.699 --> 05:35.068
YEAH, LIKE THE ACTRESS --
DELLA REESE.

05:35.068 --> 05:36.570
WHAT'S HER LAST NAME?

05:36.570 --> 05:39.206
LA REESE. LA REESE.

05:39.206 --> 05:41.609
ISN'T THAT WEIRD?

05:41.609 --> 05:43.210
CAN I HAVE DELL'S NUMBER?

05:43.210 --> 05:44.578
NO, SHE'S REALLY BUSY.

05:44.578 --> 05:47.381
IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS,
JUST ASK JACK.

05:47.381 --> 05:49.049
HE KNOWS EVERYTHING
SHE WANTS.

05:49.049 --> 05:50.050
OH, OKAY.

05:50.050 --> 05:52.920
WELL, WHAT KIND OF FLOWERS
DOES SHE LIKE?

05:52.920 --> 05:55.589
SHE LIKES CALLA LILIES
AND CANDLES

05:55.589 --> 05:58.726
AND A BAND TO PLAY OUR SONG
AFTER WE KISS.

05:58.726 --> 06:02.262
LIVE MUSIC IS GONNA BE
MORE EXPENSIVE THAN A DEEJAY.

06:02.262 --> 06:05.165
I'M IN LOVE.
MONEY'S NO OBJECT.

06:05.165 --> 06:06.834
GET A 20-PIECE ORCHESTRA.

06:07.935 --> 06:11.138
AND DOVES --
LOTS OF DOVES.

06:12.706 --> 06:17.077
WELL, IF I KNOW DELL LA REESE --
AND I DO --

06:17.077 --> 06:19.813
SHE'LL BE HAPPY
WITH JUST A SMALL BAND

06:19.813 --> 06:23.451
AND WHATEVER LOCAL BIRDS
HAPPEN TO BE FLYING BY.

06:24.718 --> 06:27.788
I CAN'T PLAN A WEDDING
UNTIL I TALK TO THE BRIDE.

06:27.788 --> 06:30.491
CAN YOU AND DELL COME OVER
TOMORROW AROUND 7:00?

06:30.491 --> 06:31.725
I...

06:31.725 --> 06:33.727
YEAH, JACK,
BRING HER AROUND 7:00.

06:33.727 --> 06:36.964
WELL, I-I DON'T KNOW
WHERE SHE IS RIGHT NOW.

06:36.964 --> 06:39.467
YOU CAN MAKE SOME CALLS, MAN,
AND FIND HER.

06:39.467 --> 06:40.768
THAT REMINDS ME --

06:40.768 --> 06:42.803
I GOTTA PICK UP
A CASE OF THAT SCOTCH

06:42.803 --> 06:45.606
SHE LIKES TO DRINK
WHILE SHE'S WATCHING BOXING.

06:45.606 --> 06:47.775
SHE ALSO LIKES CIGARS.

06:47.775 --> 06:49.910
TELL HER NOT TO PUSH IT.

06:51.979 --> 06:54.882
YOU KNOW, THE PLACE
JACK'S GETTING MARRIED

06:54.882 --> 06:57.350
HAS AN OPENING
SIX WEEKS LATER.

06:57.350 --> 06:59.920
IT WOULD BE PERFECT
FOR OUR VOW RENEWAL.

06:59.920 --> 07:01.922
IT OVERLOOKS THE OCEAN
IN MALIBU.

07:01.922 --> 07:03.857
IT'S SO BEAUTIFUL.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

07:03.857 --> 07:06.694
YEAH, THAT SOUNDS LIKE
A GOOD IDEA, ANGIE.

07:06.694 --> 07:09.597
WAITERS CARRYING TRAYS
OF SHRIMP COCKTAIL,

07:09.597 --> 07:11.965
FIGHTING OFF HUNDREDS
OF STARVING SEA GULLS.

07:11.965 --> 07:15.703
"LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
MR. AND MRS. GEORGE --"

07:15.703 --> 07:17.538
OW! EEH, EEH, EEH!

07:17.538 --> 07:19.006
OH, MY GOD -- MY EYES!

07:19.006 --> 07:24.512
THE SEA GULLS HAVE
CARRIED OFF THE BRIDE!

07:24.512 --> 07:26.680
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
HAVE THE GUTS TO SAY

07:26.680 --> 07:28.415
YOU DON'T WANT
TO REMARRY ME.

07:28.415 --> 07:30.017
ANGIE, THAT'S NOT TRUE.

07:30.017 --> 07:31.485
YES, IT IS.

07:31.485 --> 07:34.187
AND YOU SHOOT DOWN
EVERY ONE OF MY IDEAS.

07:34.187 --> 07:36.957
WHY DOES IT HAVE TO BE
EVERYTHING YOU WANT?

07:36.957 --> 07:39.159
IT'S ALWAYS
WHAT THE WOMEN WANT.

07:39.159 --> 07:42.395
I ASSUMED YOU WEREN'T
INTERESTED IN ALL THE DETAILS.

07:42.395 --> 07:43.897
WHY WOULD YOU ASSUME THAT?

07:43.897 --> 07:47.768
EVERY TIME I ASK YOU
A QUESTION, YOU ROLL YOUR EYES.

07:47.768 --> 07:51.739
BECAUSE I WAS THINKING.
ASK ME A QUESTION.

07:51.739 --> 07:54.975
DO YOU WANT THE INVITATIONS
ON VELLUM OR PARCHMENT?

07:59.279 --> 08:02.449
PARCHMENT. YOU SEE?
YOU HAD TO WAIT FOR IT!

08:02.449 --> 08:05.185
I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T KNOW.

08:05.185 --> 08:07.921
DO YOU WANT TO HELP ME
PLAN THIS?

08:12.392 --> 08:14.361
I'VE GOT A BETTER IDEA.

08:14.361 --> 08:16.096
SINCE I ASKED YOU
TO REMARRY ME,

08:16.096 --> 08:17.865
LET ME PLAN
THE WHOLE THING!

08:17.865 --> 08:21.635
HONEY,
T-THAT'S A LOT OF WORK.

08:21.635 --> 08:24.538
YOU MEAN "A LOT OF WORK
FOR A MAN."

08:24.538 --> 08:27.775
HA!
JUST SAY IT.

08:27.775 --> 08:29.643
ALL I AM TO YOU
IS A PAYCHECK

08:29.643 --> 08:33.280
AND A GUY WHO GOES DOWNSTAIRS
EVERY TIME YOU HEAR A NOISE.

08:33.280 --> 08:35.816
BY THE WAY,
EVERY TIME YOU SCREAM OUT

08:35.816 --> 08:38.686
"CAREFUL, GEORGE,
YOU DON'T HAVE A GUN,"

08:38.686 --> 08:41.054
YOU GIVE THE EDGE
TO THE CRACKHEAD.

08:41.054 --> 08:43.023
ALL RIGHT.

08:43.023 --> 08:46.193
IF YOU WANT TO DO THIS,
YOU CAN DO THIS.

08:46.193 --> 08:49.162
JUST PROMISE ME
IT'LL BE ROMANTIC.

08:49.162 --> 08:51.031
ANGIE, PLEASE.

08:51.031 --> 08:53.867
[ Screeching ]
I GOT THIS!

08:55.268 --> 08:58.471
WAIT TILL YOU SEE WHAT I GOT
PLANNED FOR VALENTINE'S DAY.

08:58.471 --> 09:01.942
THAT WAS LAST WEEK. THAT'S WHY
I TOOK YOU OUT TO DINNER.

09:01.942 --> 09:04.745
BABY, THANK YOU.
THAT WAS SO NICE.

09:04.745 --> 09:07.147
YOU JUST PLAN
JACK'S PERFECT WEDDING,

09:07.147 --> 09:10.017
AND LET ME TAKE CARE
OF OUR PERFECT WEDDING.

09:10.017 --> 09:12.252
OKAY. BYE.

09:12.252 --> 09:13.787
HELLO.

09:13.787 --> 09:16.757
GEORGE, I GOT AN IDEA
ABOUT THE FAKE BRIDE.

09:16.757 --> 09:18.291
NO MASSEUSES OR HOOKERS.

09:18.291 --> 09:27.701
OKAY, STILL LOOKING.

09:27.701 --> 09:30.503
PLEASE TELL ME
YOU FOUND A FAKE WIFE.

09:30.503 --> 09:32.940
SHE'S 80?

09:32.940 --> 09:35.475
HOW BAD WAS THE STROKE?

09:35.475 --> 09:39.179
SHE'S SUPPOSED TO TASTE CAKE.
WILL IT STAY IN HER MOUTH?

09:40.948 --> 09:43.150
I'LL STALL ANGIE
TILL TOMORROW,

09:43.150 --> 09:46.319
BUT YOU BETTER
FIND SOMEONE ELSE.

09:46.319 --> 09:48.922
IF MOM'S PLANNING
HER REAL CEREMONY,

09:48.922 --> 09:51.458
WHY ARE WE COOKING SLOPPY JOES
FOR A FAKE ONE?

09:51.458 --> 09:54.327
BECAUSE THE CRAPPIER
MOM THINKS OUR WEDDING IS,

09:54.327 --> 09:57.197
THE BETTER THE SURPRISE WILL BE
WHEN SHE SEES THE REAL THING.

09:57.197 --> 10:00.400
SO IT'S LIKE OUR COLLEGE FUND
YOU ALWAYS JOKE YOU'VE SPENT,

10:00.400 --> 10:03.336
BUT WHEN THE TIME COMES,
IT'LL REALLY BE THERE.

10:03.336 --> 10:05.205
I DON'T WANT
TO RUIN THE SURPRISE.

10:05.205 --> 10:08.809
YOU KIDS, GO UPSTAIRS
AND STUDY NOW -- OR NOT.

10:10.243 --> 10:12.813
OKAY, MY DAD'S BRINGING
THE REST OF THE CAKES

10:12.813 --> 10:14.181
FOR DELL TO TASTE.

10:14.181 --> 10:16.684
I'M GLAD I'M FINALLY
GONNA MEET HER.

10:16.684 --> 10:18.485
WE HAVE SO MANY
DECISIONS TO MAKE.

10:18.485 --> 10:22.322
ACTUALLY, DELL CAN'T MAKE IT.
SHE HAS TO WORK.

10:22.322 --> 10:25.926
WHAT? THE WEDDING'S IN A WEEK.
CAN'T SHE GET OFF ONE NIGHT?

10:25.926 --> 10:26.994
UH...

10:26.994 --> 10:30.664
SHE'S A NURSE...
FOR SICK BABIES.

10:30.664 --> 10:32.032
REALLY SICK BABIES --

10:32.032 --> 10:34.001
THEY'RE LIKE --
[ CROAKS, COUGHS ]

10:34.001 --> 10:36.269
I GUESS SHE COULD
STICK THEM IN A PILE

10:36.269 --> 10:39.272
SO SHE COULD COME
TASTE SOME CAKE.

10:39.272 --> 10:41.675
SELFISH SICK BABY-HATER.

10:41.675 --> 10:45.445
I'M SORRY. IT'S JUST THIS
WEDDING IS COMING UP FAST.

10:45.445 --> 10:48.381
I'LL TALK TO JACK, AND MAYBE
DELL CAN GET OFF WORK TOMORROW.

10:48.381 --> 10:51.752
SIT DOWN. I WANT YOU TO TASTE
SOMETHING FOR OUR CEREMONY.

10:53.687 --> 10:55.756
I PRESENT...

10:55.756 --> 10:57.791
OUR FIRST COURSE.

10:59.727 --> 11:00.828
SLOPPY JOES?

11:00.828 --> 11:02.329
NO, ANGIE.

11:02.329 --> 11:06.299
WITH BUNS THIS FIRM AND TASTY,
THOSE ARE SLOPPY GEORGES!

11:06.299 --> 11:09.169
YOU CAN'T SERVE SLOPPY JOES
AT OUR RECEPTION.

11:09.169 --> 11:11.705
ALL OUR GUESTS
ARE GONNA BE DRESSED UP.

11:11.705 --> 11:13.741
ALL OUR GUESTS
ARE GONNA BE WEARING

11:13.741 --> 11:15.208
HAWAIIAN SHIRTS AND SHORTS,

11:15.208 --> 11:17.610
BECAUSE WE'RE HAVING
A BEACH WEDDING!

11:17.610 --> 11:19.379
YOU BOOKED
THE PLACE IN MALIBU?!

11:19.379 --> 11:22.750
BETTER -- I GOT THE SHRINERS
TO GIVE ME THEIR PARKING LOT.

11:22.750 --> 11:24.651
I'M GETTING
A TRUCKLOAD OF SAND.

11:24.651 --> 11:25.919
IT'S GONNA BE TROPICAL.

11:27.587 --> 11:28.956
THIS IS ALMOST AS BAD

11:28.956 --> 11:31.658
AS THE MEXICAN THEME
OF THE FIRST WEDDING.

11:31.658 --> 11:34.061
THAT WASN'T A THEME.
THAT WAS MY FAMILY.

11:37.064 --> 11:40.734
SWEETHEART, THIS ISN'T
EXACTLY WHAT I HAD IN MIND.

11:40.734 --> 11:43.236
I KNOW, ANGIE,
BUT I'M SO EXCITED.

11:43.236 --> 11:46.173
I CAN'T WAIT TO MARRY YOU AGAIN.
I LOVE YOU.

11:46.173 --> 11:47.875
OH...

11:47.875 --> 11:51.011
I GUESS...IF YOU'RE HAPPY,
THEN I'M HAPPY.

11:51.011 --> 11:53.280
GREAT. I NEED YOUR HELP
PICKING A WEDDING SINGER.

11:53.280 --> 11:56.249
I CALLED AN AGENCY.
THEY'RE GONNA SEND PEOPLE OVER.

11:56.249 --> 11:58.351
ARE THEY AT LEAST
GONNA SING OUR SONG?

11:58.351 --> 12:01.188
OF COURSE, BABY.
IT'S GONNA BE BEAUTIFUL.

12:03.723 --> 12:05.826
[ "ENDLESS LOVE" PLAYS ]

12:08.661 --> 12:11.064
HELLO?
[ LAUGHS ]

12:13.533 --> 12:17.170
* MY LOVE

12:17.170 --> 12:21.942
* THERE'S ONLY YOU IN MY LIFE

12:21.942 --> 12:24.211
* THE ONLY THING THAT'S BRIGHT

12:24.211 --> 12:26.713
PICK IT UP.
WE HAVE A SHOW IN APRIL.

12:26.713 --> 12:29.682
* MY FIRST LOVE

12:29.682 --> 12:32.953
* YOU'RE EVERY BREATH I TAKE

12:32.953 --> 12:36.924
* EVERY STEP I MAKE

12:39.159 --> 12:40.994
* AND I

12:42.796 --> 12:44.898
I'M KIND OF HUNGRY.

12:48.535 --> 12:53.773
* NO ONE ELSE
WOULD TELL ABOUT YOUR EYES *

12:53.773 --> 12:55.408
[ AIR BLOWING ]

12:55.408 --> 12:58.045
* YOUR EYES
TELL ME HOW MUCH YOU CARE *

12:58.045 --> 13:00.347
* THEY TELL ME HOW MUCH

13:00.347 --> 13:02.149
I WANT MORE.

13:02.149 --> 13:05.718
* YOU'LL ALWAYS BE

13:05.718 --> 13:09.957
* MY ENDLESS LOVE

13:12.692 --> 13:14.862
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

13:14.862 --> 13:17.764
* I TOOK ONE LOOK AT YOU

13:17.764 --> 13:20.267
* AND EVERY DREAM CAME TRUE

13:20.267 --> 13:24.004
* I COULD BE CRAZY,
BUT I'M NOT *

13:26.206 --> 13:28.842
* A LOVELY MELODY

13:28.842 --> 13:31.511
* THAT STIRS INSIDE OF ME

13:31.511 --> 13:35.815
* THIS KIND OF CRAZY
HITS THE SPOT *

13:35.815 --> 13:38.751
THIS ISN'T
"ENDLESS LOVE."

13:38.751 --> 13:41.154
WHO CARES, ANGIE?
IT'S MAGIC!

13:41.154 --> 13:44.391
CLAY AIKEN, MY ASS!

13:44.391 --> 13:48.028
* HEAVEN KNOWS
MY HEART'S ON FIRE *

13:48.028 --> 13:52.499
* MY FIRST LOVE

13:52.499 --> 13:56.904
* YOU ARE EVERY BREATH
THAT I TAKE *

13:56.904 --> 14:01.909
HE'S, LIKE, A HUGE STAR
IN FRANCE.

14:01.909 --> 14:04.912
* I-I-I-I

14:04.912 --> 14:07.881
* I WANT TO SHARE

14:07.881 --> 14:13.320
* ALL MY LOVE WITH YOU

14:13.320 --> 14:17.757
* NO ONE ELSE WILL DO

14:17.757 --> 14:20.227
* AND YOUR EYES

14:20.227 --> 14:21.628
* YOUR EYES, YOUR EYES

14:21.628 --> 14:24.531
* THEY TELL ME
HOW MUCH YOU CARE *

14:24.531 --> 14:26.233
IT'S LIKE KISS.

14:26.233 --> 14:29.836
THEY'RE MINIKISS, ANGIE.
THEY'RE TRAVEL-SIZE.

14:29.836 --> 14:34.074
* YOU WILL ALWAYS BE

14:34.074 --> 14:38.578
* MY ENDLESS LOVE

14:45.185 --> 14:48.755
[ High-pitched ]
* TWO HEARTS

14:48.755 --> 14:53.093
* TWO HEARTS THAT BEAT AS ONE

14:53.093 --> 14:56.796
* OUR LIVES HAVE JUST BEGUN

14:56.796 --> 14:58.999
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

14:58.999 --> 15:02.970
[ Deep voice ]
* FOREVER

15:02.970 --> 15:06.974
* I'LL HOLD YOU CLOSE
IN MY ARMS *

15:06.974 --> 15:12.879
* I CAN'T RESIST YOUR CHARMS

15:12.879 --> 15:17.084
* AND YES

15:17.084 --> 15:22.122
* I'LL BE A FOOL FOR YOU

15:22.122 --> 15:25.592
* I'M SURE

15:25.592 --> 15:27.060
BOOM, BOOM, BOOM, BOOM.

15:27.060 --> 15:29.662
* IN YOUR EYES

15:29.662 --> 15:35.668
* I CAN DO ANYTHING
'CAUSE I KNOW *

15:35.668 --> 15:37.804
BOOM, BOOM, BOOM, BOOM.

15:37.804 --> 15:40.007
BOOM, BOOM, BOOM, BOOM.

15:40.007 --> 15:43.843
* IN YOUR EYES

15:43.843 --> 15:47.014
* I CAN DO ANYTHING

15:47.014 --> 15:51.018
* 'CAUSE I KNOW THAT I'M HAPPY

15:51.018 --> 15:54.054
* 'CAUSE IT'S MY ANNIVERSARY
TODAY *

15:54.054 --> 15:56.756
* IN YOUR EYES

15:56.756 --> 15:58.725
[ PLAYING "ENDLESS LOVE" ]

16:02.862 --> 16:05.765
SHE'S GOOD -- BUT KEEP IN MIND,
IF WE BOOK HER,

16:05.765 --> 16:08.735
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO PAY
THROUGH THE NOSE!

16:08.735 --> 16:10.370
[ LAUGHS ]

16:24.184 --> 16:26.353
THANKS FOR COMING!

16:31.424 --> 16:35.295
WHEW!
HARD TO CHOOSE, HUH?

16:35.295 --> 16:36.963
YEAH.

16:36.963 --> 16:38.531
IF YOU CAN'T DECIDE,

16:38.531 --> 16:42.069
I COULD BRING THEM ALL BACK,
AND THEY COULD SING AGAIN.

16:42.069 --> 16:46.273
JUST TELL RIP TAYLOR
HE'S GOT THE GIG.

16:55.582 --> 16:59.052
JACK, WHERE'S YOUR BRIDE?
YOU WERE GONNA PICK HER UP.

16:59.052 --> 17:00.353
A LITTLE PROBLEM.

17:00.353 --> 17:03.190
YOU SAID YOUR COUSIN
WOULD DO IT FOR $200.

17:03.190 --> 17:05.291
WHEN SHE FOUND OUT
WE MIGHT HAVE TO KISS

17:05.291 --> 17:07.260
TO MAKE IT SEEM REAL,
SHE FREAKED OUT.

17:07.260 --> 17:09.362
APPARENTLY,
IT WAS FINE WHEN WE WERE 13,

17:09.362 --> 17:13.700
BUT NOW THAT SHE'S MARRIED
AND GOT KIDS, IT'S SICK.

17:13.700 --> 17:16.536
ANGIE'S GONNA BE HERE
ANY SECOND. I'M SCREWED.

17:16.536 --> 17:18.305
MAYBE I COULD GET
ONE OF THE WORKERS.

17:18.305 --> 17:20.973
ANGIE KNOWS ALL OF THEM.
WHAT ABOUT ONE OF THE TEMPS?

17:20.973 --> 17:22.409
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

17:22.409 --> 17:24.144
SHE'S HERE.
HURRY, HURRY, HURRY.

17:24.144 --> 17:26.579
WHAT DO I SAY
TO THE TEMP?

17:26.579 --> 17:28.915
OFFER HER $200 TO BE
YOUR WIFE FOR THE NIGHT.

17:28.915 --> 17:31.050
BUT DON'T MAKE IT
SOUND CREEPY.

17:32.585 --> 17:33.853
HI, HONEY.

17:33.853 --> 17:36.989
WE COULD TAKE ONE CAR
TO THE LOCATION IN MALIBU.

17:36.989 --> 17:38.758
IS DELL HERE YET?

17:38.758 --> 17:42.061
YEAH, SHE'S HERE. SHE MUST
HAVE SNUCK OFF WITH JACK.

17:42.061 --> 17:46.099
THOSE LOVEBIRDS -- THEY CAN'T
KEEP THEIR HANDS OFF EACH OTHER.

17:46.099 --> 17:50.170
ANGIE, MEET
MY LOVELY FIANCÃ©E, DELL.

17:50.170 --> 17:53.606
WHAT A...

17:53.606 --> 17:56.409
WHAT'S UP?

17:56.409 --> 17:58.878
IT'S NICE
TO FINALLY MEET YOU.

17:58.878 --> 18:00.713
OW!

18:00.713 --> 18:03.015
I'M SORRY WE'RE LATE.
I WENT LOOKING FOR DELL.

18:03.015 --> 18:04.751
I FOUND HER
BY THE LOADING DOCK.

18:04.751 --> 18:07.854
SO, WHY DON'T WE SEE
THAT WEDDING SITE?

18:07.854 --> 18:08.988
WHATEVER.

18:08.988 --> 18:10.623
OKAY, HONEY.

18:10.623 --> 18:13.092
WHAT DID I SAY
ABOUT THE TOUCHING?

18:14.961 --> 18:16.763
TRADITIONAL GAL --
WHOO!

18:16.763 --> 18:19.966
NO TOUCHING UNTIL
THE WEDDING NIGHT.

18:19.966 --> 18:22.101
DID YOU JUST
CALL ME "GAL?"

18:22.101 --> 18:24.471
WHY DON'T WE TAKE
TWO CARS.

18:24.471 --> 18:27.106
THAT OKAY WITH YOU, DUDE?
GO, GO, GO.

18:30.710 --> 18:33.280
THAT WAS A GOOD IDEA.
MALIBU IS BEAUTIFUL.

18:33.280 --> 18:34.914
OH, I KNOW.

18:34.914 --> 18:38.751
THAT'S ACTUALLY WHERE I WANTED
TO GET MARRIED.

18:38.751 --> 18:41.188
HONEY, YOU'RE NOT
THE ONLY PRINCESS

18:41.188 --> 18:42.855
WHO'S HAVING A SPECIAL DAY.

18:47.227 --> 18:49.296
WHAT?
YOU WEREN'T EATING IT.

18:52.632 --> 18:56.303
DELL, I SEE YOU LIKE THAT CAKE.
IS THAT YOUR FAVORITE?

18:56.303 --> 18:57.970
I DON'T KNOW.
WHICH ONE DO YOU LIKE?

18:57.970 --> 19:00.707
WELL, THE LEMON'S MY FAVORITE,
BUT THE CHOCOLATE --

19:00.707 --> 19:03.476
LEMON, IT IS.
LET'S KEEP THIS MOVING.

19:09.316 --> 19:11.651
SUGAR AND SPICE
AND EVERYTHING NICE.

19:11.651 --> 19:14.221
YOU HOOKED A GOOD ONE, JACK.
WHAT'S NEXT?

19:14.221 --> 19:16.823
WELL, IF YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE A PRIEST,

19:16.823 --> 19:19.826
I NEED TO KNOW IF YOU'RE
WRITING YOUR OWN VOWS.

19:19.826 --> 19:23.663
KEEP IN MIND, IT'S A WAY
TO PERSONALIZE THE CEREMONY

19:23.663 --> 19:27.334
AND SAY EXACTLY WHAT
YOU FEEL ABOUT EACH OTHER.

19:34.374 --> 19:38.478
OR YOU COULD JUST SAY
"I DO."

19:38.478 --> 19:40.146
WHY DON'T WE
CALL IT A NIGHT.

19:40.146 --> 19:43.383
IF I HAVE ANY MORE QUESTIONS,
I'LL CALL YOU TOMORROW.

19:43.383 --> 19:44.684
FINE BY ME.

19:44.684 --> 19:47.920
GOOD NIGHT, JACK.
NICE TO MEET YOU, DELL.

19:51.824 --> 19:54.361
THIS IS A HUGE MISTAKE.
THEY SHOULDN'T GET MARRIED.

19:54.361 --> 19:55.862
THERE'S NO CHEMISTRY.

19:55.862 --> 19:57.764
THEY BARELY EVEN
KNOW EACH OTHER.

19:57.764 --> 20:01.067
YOU'RE A WEDDING PLANNER.
JUST DO THE WEDDING.

20:01.067 --> 20:03.236
YOU'VE KNOWN JACK
FOR 15 YEARS.

20:03.236 --> 20:06.072
THIS WOMAN IS COMPLETELY
WRONG FOR HIM.

20:06.072 --> 20:07.674
YOU'RE QUIET FOR TWO HOURS

20:07.674 --> 20:09.709
AFTER WATCHING
"BEAUTY AND THE BEAST,"

20:09.709 --> 20:13.946
YET WHEN IT HAPPENS IN YOUR
KITCHEN, YOU DON'T BELIEVE IT.

20:13.946 --> 20:17.284
GEORGE, THIS IS NOT
JUST A PAYCHECK FOR ME.

20:17.284 --> 20:20.086
I LIKE TO MAKE
PEOPLE'S DREAMS COME TRUE.

20:20.086 --> 20:23.356
IF THEY'RE NOT IN LOVE,
I DON'T WANT TO MARRY THEM.

20:23.356 --> 20:25.992
WHAT'S LOVE GOT TO DO
WITH MARRIAGE, ANYWAY?

20:25.992 --> 20:28.295
HEAR ME OUT.

20:28.295 --> 20:29.829
WHAT ABOUT INDIA, HUH?

20:29.829 --> 20:33.666
EVERY MARRIAGE IS ARRANGED --
NOT ONE PERSON IN LOVE.

20:33.666 --> 20:36.503
AND YET THEY HAVE A BILLION
PEOPLE, SO IT'S WORKING.

20:36.503 --> 20:40.573
IT ALSO PROVES THAT
YOU CAN HAVE SEX WITHOUT LOVE.

20:40.573 --> 20:43.810
BUT I'M NOT READY
TO HAVE THAT ARGUMENT YET.

20:43.810 --> 20:46.479
I'M STILL PUTTING TOGETHER
ALL THE EVIDENCE.

20:51.651 --> 20:53.986
GEORGE, I'M NOT
CHANGING MY MIND.

20:53.986 --> 20:57.390
IT WOULD BE A HUGE MISTAKE.
I'M NOT DOING THIS WEDDING.

20:57.390 --> 21:01.060
HEY, YOU WON'T BELIEVE THIS.
JACK IS IN THE DRIVEWAY.

21:01.060 --> 21:04.964
HE'S HAVING A FIGHT WITH
SOME DUDE ON A MOTORCYCLE.

21:06.933 --> 21:08.167
NOT NOW, MOM.

21:08.167 --> 21:13.272
OKAY, OKAY, BUT HE IS GETTING
HIS ASS KICKED.

21:13.272 --> 21:15.542
ANGIE, I DON'T THINK
YOU UNDERSTAND.

21:15.542 --> 21:17.844
THIS IS MY BOSS.
YOU CAN'T BACK OUT NOW.

21:17.844 --> 21:20.880
OKAY, FINE.
I'LL DO IT FOR YOUR BOSS.

21:20.880 --> 21:23.550
BUT I AM REALLY
DISAPPOINTED IN YOU.

21:23.550 --> 21:24.917
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

21:24.917 --> 21:27.320
YOU'RE JUST DOING THIS
TO KEEP JACK HAPPY.

21:27.320 --> 21:29.055
YOU DON'T CARE
IF HE'S IN LOVE.

21:29.055 --> 21:31.724
YOU DON'T HAVE
A ROMANTIC BONE IN YOUR BODY.

21:31.724 --> 21:33.125
I'M ROMANTIC!

21:33.125 --> 21:37.630
WHO PUT ON MOOD MUSIC
LAST TIME WE MADE LOVE?

21:37.630 --> 21:40.800
YOU PUT ON CARTOONS.

21:40.800 --> 21:43.069
I DIDN'T HEAR YOU
COMPLAINING.

21:43.069 --> 21:47.607
[ High-pitched ]
BOOP!

21:47.607 --> 21:50.943
AND NEITHER ARE SLOPPY JOES,
HAWAIIAN SHIRTS,

21:50.943 --> 21:53.813
OR A FAKE BEACH
IN THE SHRINERS' PARKING LOT.

21:53.813 --> 21:56.683
WHAT THE HELL KIND OF
VOW RENEWAL IS THAT?

21:56.683 --> 21:58.351
I DON'T BELIEVE YOU!

21:58.351 --> 22:01.320
THIS IS THE CEREMONY
YOU'VE PLANNED

22:01.320 --> 22:03.189
FOR THE WOMAN YOU LOVE?

22:03.189 --> 22:05.425
THANK YOU, BENNY.

22:05.425 --> 22:07.427
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT ROMANCE?

22:07.427 --> 22:08.995
YOU JUST SWING ON A TIRE

22:08.995 --> 22:11.698
TILL THE ZOOKEEPER BRINGS
ANOTHER MALE INTO YOUR CAGE.

22:11.698 --> 22:14.834
YOU KNOW WHAT HURTS
THE MOST?

22:14.834 --> 22:17.937
YOU DON'T REALIZE WHAT
THIS VOW RENEWAL MEANS TO ME.

22:17.937 --> 22:20.373
IT MAY BE JUST A BIG PARTY
TO YOU, BUT TO ME,

22:20.373 --> 22:24.210
IT WAS THE BEAUTIFUL WEDDING
WE COULDN'T AFFORD 18 YEARS AGO.

22:24.210 --> 22:25.845
ANGIE, COME ON.
TRUST ME.

22:25.845 --> 22:28.347
IT'S NOT GONNA BE
AS BAD AS YOU THINK.

22:28.347 --> 22:30.082
IT'S GONNA BE WORSE.

22:30.082 --> 22:31.451
Y-YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.

22:31.451 --> 22:33.753
MAYBE I PLANNED
SOMETHING ROMANTIC.

22:33.753 --> 22:36.288
YEAH, LIKE WHAT?
TELL ME.

22:36.288 --> 22:37.790
TELL HER, GEORGE.

22:40.092 --> 22:41.594
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

22:41.594 --> 22:43.796
IF YOU'RE NOT GONNA TELL HER,
THEN I WILL.

22:43.796 --> 22:44.931
MOM!

22:44.931 --> 22:48.200
I HEAR THE BRIDESMAIDS
ARE WEARING COCONUT BRAS,

22:48.200 --> 22:52.439
AND THE PORTA-POTTIES ARE
BEING DECORATED LIKE TIKI HUTS.

22:53.940 --> 22:56.943
YOU KNOW I CAN'T GO
IN A CHEMICAL TOILET!

23:04.350 --> 23:06.152
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

23:09.088 --> 23:10.623
DAD, DAD.

23:10.623 --> 23:13.860
I WROTE A POEM THAT I'D LIKE
TO READ DURING THE CEREMONY.

23:13.860 --> 23:15.795
THAT'S SO NICE.
DID YOU MEMORIZE IT?

23:15.795 --> 23:17.897
NO.
IT'S ON HERE.

23:17.897 --> 23:20.533
THAT'S GREAT.
I CAN'T WAIT.

23:20.533 --> 23:22.969
Hey, Max.

23:22.969 --> 23:26.539
YOUR SISTER'S GOT A POEM.
YOU KNOW WHAT TO DO.

23:26.539 --> 23:28.407
FIND IT. EAT IT.

23:31.444 --> 23:35.815
LET ME KNOW
THE SECOND SHE GETS HERE.

23:35.815 --> 23:37.917
WELL,
DELL STILL ISN'T HERE.

23:37.917 --> 23:40.352
I TOLD YOU
THIS WAS A HUGE MISTAKE.

23:40.352 --> 23:41.754
I AGREE.

23:41.754 --> 23:44.090
THAT IS WAY TOO MUCH MONEY
TO WASTE ON TWO PEOPLE

23:44.090 --> 23:46.926
WHO SHOULDN'T HAVE GOTTEN
MARRIED IN THE FIRST PLACE.

23:46.926 --> 23:49.028
YOU'LL SEE WHAT I MEAN
LATER.

23:49.028 --> 23:50.963
SIT DOWN, BAT!

23:53.432 --> 23:54.867
YOU KNOW, HONEY,

23:54.867 --> 23:57.870
YOU LOOK ABSOLUTELY
BEAUTIFUL TODAY.

23:57.870 --> 24:00.039
OF COURSE
I LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

24:00.039 --> 24:02.709
THIS WHOLE PLACE
LOOKS BEAUTIFUL

24:02.709 --> 24:05.411
BECAUSE I PLANNED
THE PERFECT WEDDING --

24:05.411 --> 24:07.313
EXCEPT THERE'S NO BRIDE.

24:07.313 --> 24:08.581
WHERE THE HELL IS DELL?

24:08.581 --> 24:10.016
J-JUST CALM DOWN.

24:10.016 --> 24:13.352
DON'T TELL ME TO CALM DOWN.
YOU KNOW I HATE THAT.

24:13.352 --> 24:16.188
BABY, RELAX.

24:16.188 --> 24:17.223
OH, THAT'S BETTER.

24:17.223 --> 24:19.025
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

24:19.025 --> 24:22.194
LET'S DO THIS
BEFORE I CHANGE MY MIND.

24:22.194 --> 24:23.395
DO WHAT?

24:23.395 --> 24:25.865
YOU'LL SEE WHAT I MEAN
LATER.

24:25.865 --> 24:27.767
WHY DOES EVERYONE
KEEP SAYING THAT?

24:27.767 --> 24:30.136
YOU'LL SEE
IN ONE DAMN MINUTE!

24:31.638 --> 24:33.172
[ "THE WEDDING MARCH" PLAYS ]

24:33.172 --> 24:36.743
WHAT MORON CUED THE BAND?
CUT THE MUSIC.

24:36.743 --> 24:38.711
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

24:38.711 --> 24:41.781
DADDY.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

24:41.781 --> 24:44.784
I'M HERE TO WALK YOU
DOWN THE AISLE.

24:44.784 --> 24:46.619
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

24:46.619 --> 24:49.622
THIS IS
YOUR WEDDING-VOW RENEWAL.

24:49.622 --> 24:52.158
GEORGE DID THIS
ALL FOR YOU.

25:11.477 --> 25:13.813
[ Voice breaking ]
CUE THE MUSIC.

25:13.813 --> 25:17.617
[ "THE WEDDING MARCH" RESUMES ]

25:38.270 --> 25:40.206
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

25:46.078 --> 25:49.048
THIS WHOLE TIME,
YOU WERE TRICKING ME?

25:50.382 --> 25:52.018
YEAH.

25:53.285 --> 25:55.087
OHH!

25:56.689 --> 25:59.091
I LOVE YOU.

26:01.828 --> 26:03.963
YOU KNOW, ANGIE...

26:03.963 --> 26:06.833
THE FIRST TIME
WE GOT MARRIED,

26:06.833 --> 26:10.169
I KEPT THINKING,
"I DON'T DESERVE YOU."

26:10.169 --> 26:13.305
AND NOW,
AFTER 18 AMAZING YEARS,

26:13.305 --> 26:16.308
I KNOW THAT...I DON'T.

26:18.077 --> 26:20.212
I'M THE LUCKIEST GUY
IN THE WORLD.

26:20.212 --> 26:23.149
AND...I LOVE YOU.

26:25.084 --> 26:28.788
IF YOU WOULD JUST STOP
TRYING TO GO GOLFING WITH ME

26:28.788 --> 26:32.124
AND REALIZE THAT IT'S MY TIME
AWAY FROM YOU...

26:34.060 --> 26:37.764
...WE WOULD HAVE
THE PERFECT MARRIAGE.

26:39.231 --> 26:41.100
I LOVE YOU, BABY.

26:56.348 --> 26:59.551
I'D LIKE TO INTRODUCE YOU
TO A GOOD FRIEND OF MINE --

26:59.551 --> 27:02.221
ROBERT RODRIGUEZ
AND HIS BAND.

27:03.990 --> 27:06.859
I WANT TO DEDICATE THIS SONG
TO GEORGE AND ANGIE.

27:06.859 --> 27:08.560
WHEN I FIRST MET THEM --

27:08.560 --> 27:11.597
JUST SHUT UP AND PLAY!

27:11.597 --> 27:13.833
I GUESS THE BAR IS OPEN.

27:13.833 --> 27:16.903
NAH, SHE KEEPS A FLASK
IN HER GIRDLE.

27:16.903 --> 27:18.738
[ ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ]

27:18.738 --> 27:21.307
[ SINGING IN SPANISH ]

27:45.364 --> 27:46.065
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]
